# Placeholder so the `kestra/workflows/` directory exists in every
# user's workspace Gitea repo from the first deploy.
#
# Why this file is here:
# `system.git-sync` (the Kestra flow registered by deploy.sh) pulls
# helper files from this directory every 15 minutes via the
# SyncNamespaceFiles plugin. The plugin throws
# `IllegalArgumentException: The directory 'kestra/workflows' was
# not found in the git repository` and the run lands in FAILED
# state when the directory is missing — flooding the Kestra
# execution list with red dots even on a perfectly healthy stack.
#
# This .gitkeep gets seeded by `scripts/deploy.sh` like any other
# file under `examples/workspace-seeds/`, materialising
# `kestra/workflows/.gitkeep` in the fork. SyncNamespaceFiles
# then sees an empty (but existent) directory and runs to SUCCESS.
#
# What goes in this directory:
# Helper files that flows reference at runtime — Python scripts,
# SQL templates, configs, JSON fixtures. NOT flow definitions
# (those go in `kestra/flows/` and are pulled by `system.flow-sync`).
# Once you add a real file here, this .gitkeep can be deleted, but
# leaving it is fine — the Kestra plugin ignores dotfiles when
# materialising files into the namespace's file area.
